originalText.text: Dr. Rapaport and his team are amazing! I went to him for a breast augmentation, and I couldn’t be more pleased with the results. From the consultation to the end of the surgery, Dr. Rapaport has been there to ensure the highest quality of care and has addressed any questions/concerns I’ve had. One of my biggest concerns was scarring, and I don't have any! He’ll provide professional input to help you make decisions, but overall, emphasize that the most important thing is that you'll like it. Thank you, Dr. Rapaport, for everything! If you want a talented surgeon to do the job, go to him.

originalText.text: From start to finish enough cannot be said about the kindness and caring of both the staff at Dr Rapaport’s office and Dr Rapaport himself. The immediate and thorough responses to calls, emails and text is outstanding from initial contact right through surgery and after care. Incredibly impressive. Dr Rapaport was recommended highly and 4 months after surgery it is obvious why. I could not be happier with the .surgery.   Dr Rapaport’s skills and knowledge yielded results that are truly transforming. He listened as we talked about what it was I was looking to attain and he  went above my expectations. Dr Rapaport is a compassionate and gifted surgeon.

originalText.text: I had Daxxify treatment to my jaw and trapezius muscles from Dr. Rapaport. It hasn’t even been 24 hours and I feel like a new person. The Daxxify works so much quicker than Botox. After a year of extreme tension in both areas it’s completely gone. This is life changing. My posture is better, I can move without pain and I can even breathe easier. For anyone with neck tension this is a game changer. I believe doing both my jaw and neck/trapezius areas at the same time made a huge difference. I cannot recommend this treatment enough. Not just for aesthetic reasons but quality of life although my neck already looks much thinner and longer. It hasn’t even been a day so I know it will only get better. I’m so happy I did this. I was not expecting the results to be this amazing. Thank you Dr. Rapaport!

originalText.text:
As a prospective patient for breast augmentation, I called Dr. Rapaport’s office (along with several others) with questions such as ballpark costs for a breast augmentation. My concern was not only finding a competent surgeon but also a surgeon I could trust and within my budget. Calling these offices helped answer my questions and gave me a sense on how I should finance consultation fees. At Dr. Rapaport’s office, Samantha, advised me the costs would be non-refundable $500 for a breast augmentation consultation and that if I was to move forward, that $500 could be used toward my overall augmentation procedure. Samantha quoted the augmentation at $13-$15k. As a prospective patient, this was in line of my budget so I went ahead and booked the $500 non-refundable consultation. In my research, I have found this to be a common practice in plastic surgeon’s offices so nothing jumped out at me as odd.

Now in hindsight I could have asked more questions but as a new patient, it should be the doctor’s office who should disclose all potential costs upfront. Similar to other plastic surgeons offices, Dr. Rapaport’s office provided me a cost range, therefore I trusted their professional representation of their services.

In person, Dr. Rapaport was wonderful to speak with, he answered all my questions and then some. I felt comfortable with him as my surgeon. He’s competent, experienced, and has wonderful bedside manners. However, at the end of my consultation, I was quoted for an underarm breast augmentation of $26k! This is nearly double the quote I was given over the phone via Samantha at Dr. Rapaport’s office! Not only did I find out after the fact, but I walked out extremely disappointed because I spent $500 on a non-refundable consultation for a doctor and procedure that I didn’t know I couldn’t afford. I can understand estimate ranges are still ballparks but should still be within 10-20%. I kindly asked for the $500 to be refunded and even offered to compromise for a partial refund. However, after multiple email and phone call attempts, I was told (although kindly) that any refund was not possible by the staff. I also have no way to confirm if they spoke with Dr. Rapaport directly on this matter either. Even if the staff unintentionally misguided me on the cost, at a minimum, the office should take responsibility of this error and aim to correct it. I did not feel this was attempted in the slightest.

Although Dr. Rapaport is a highly intelligent and qualified surgeon for your plastic surgery needs, I must warn you of the staff. I cannot trust that the team is aware of his costs and even if they are then they should accurately guide a prospective patient of all potential costs before a non-refundable fee is paid. So I cannot trust that the team would be the best in my care, especially under anesthesia. Please look elsewhere for your plastic surgery needs. Not only should the surgeon be the best for your needs, financially within your budget, but the staff should also be the best in your care.
